---
import Breadcrumb from '../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
	title="Support — Auto-Coursera Help, Bugs & Community Resources"
	description="Get help with Auto-Coursera. Find troubleshooting guides, report bugs, request features, and connect with the community."
	canonicalPath="/support/"
>
	<!-- ================================================================
	     HERO
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="hero" data-bg="deep" aria-labelledby="support-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<p class="hero__product">Auto-Coursera — AI-powered Coursera quiz assistant</p>
			<Breadcrumb items={[{ label: 'Home', href: '/' }, { label: 'Support' }]} />
			<h1 id="support-heading">Support</h1>
			<p class="hero__lead">
				Troubleshooting guides, bug reporting, feature requests,
				and community resources — all in one place.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     QUICK HELP
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="void" aria-labelledby="quickhelp-heading">
		<div class="container">
			<h2 id="quickhelp-heading">Quick help</h2>
			<div class="help-grid">
				<a href="/docs/" class="help-card">
					<h3>Getting Started</h3>
					<p>First-time setup and overview of features.</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/docs/troubleshoot/" class="help-card">
					<h3>Troubleshooting</h3>
					<p>Common problems and how to fix them.</p>
				</a>
				<a href="/docs/setup/" class="help-card">
					<h3>API Setup</h3>
					<p>How to get and configure an AI provider API key.</p>
				</a>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     COMMON ISSUES
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="deep" aria-labelledby="issues-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="issues-heading">Common issues</h2>

		<details class="faq-item" id="faq-technical-issues">
			<summary>Having technical issues?</summary>
				<div class="faq-body">
					<p>
						For step-by-step solutions to common problems — the extension
						not loading, API key errors, browser compatibility, detection
						issues, and more — see our dedicated
						<a href="/docs/troubleshoot/">Troubleshooting guide</a>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</details>

		<details class="faq-item" id="faq-auto-update">
			<summary>Does it auto-update?</summary>
				<div class="faq-body">
					<p>
						Yes. The extension checks for updates every 6 hours
						using Chromium's built-in extension update mechanism.
						Updates are downloaded and applied automatically — no
						action required on your part.
					</p>
					<p>
						You can also manually check for updates from the
						extension popup or from <code>chrome://extensions</code>.
					</p>
				</div>
			</details>

		<details class="faq-item" id="faq-wrong-or-low-confidence">
			<summary>The answers seem wrong or low confidence</summary>
				<div class="faq-body">
				<p>
					Answer accuracy depends on your AI provider and model.
					The extension uses color-coded highlights to communicate confidence:
				</p>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>High confidence ✓</strong> (green highlight) — score ≥ 0.8. The model is fairly sure, but still verify before submitting.</li>
					<li><strong>Review suggested ~</strong> (yellow highlight) — score 0.5–0.8. The model is less certain; worth checking.</li>
					<li><strong>Low confidence !</strong> (red highlight) — score &lt; 0.5. The model is guessing. Always verify these manually.</li>
				</ul>
				<p>
					A red highlight can also indicate an API error or timeout rather than a confidence judgment.
					If you see red on every answer, check your API key and network connection.
					For the full confidence model, see the <a href="/docs/#what-to-expect">Getting Started guide</a>.
				</p>
				<p>Some tips for improving results:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Try a different provider — some models handle certain question types better than others.</li>
					<li>The extension works best with multiple-choice and true/false questions.
						See <a href="/docs/#supported-question-types">supported question types</a>
						for the full list.</li>
					<li>Raise the confidence threshold in settings to only auto-select answers the model is more sure about.</li>
				</ul>
					<p>For detailed troubleshooting, see the <a href="/docs/troubleshoot/#faq-wrong-answers">answers seem wrong</a> guide.</p>
				</div>
			</details>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     REPORT A BUG
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="void" aria-labelledby="bugs-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="bugs-heading">Report a bug</h2>
			<p>
				Found something broken? Open an issue on GitHub and we'll look
				into it.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					Open a GitHub Issue
				</a>
			</p>

			<h3>What to include in your report</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Your browser name and version (e.g., Chrome 124.0)</li>
				<li>The extension version (shown in the popup)</li>
				<li>Any error messages you see (check the browser console with <kbd>F12</kbd>)</li>
				<li>Steps to reproduce the problem</li>
				<li>What you expected to happen vs. what actually happened</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>New to GitHub?</h3>
			<p>
				GitHub Issues is a public tracker where anyone can report
				problems. You'll need a free
				<a href="https://github.com/signup" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub account</a>.
				Click <strong>"New issue"</strong> on the
				<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">issues page</a>,
				describe the problem, and submit. We'll respond on the same thread.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     REQUEST A FEATURE
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="deep" aria-labelledby="features-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="features-heading">Request a feature</h2>
			<p>
				Have an idea for something Auto-Coursera should do? We'd like to
				hear it.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					Open a GitHub Issue
				</a>
			</p>

			<h3>What makes a good request</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>Describe the problem</strong>, not just the solution. "I can't tell which answers are auto-selected" is more useful than "add a checkmark icon."</li>
				<li><strong>Give context.</strong> When and why do you need this? What workflow does it improve?</li>
				<li><strong>Be specific.</strong> "Better UI" is hard to act on. "The popup text is too small on 4K displays" is actionable.</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     SECURITY
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="void" aria-labelledby="security-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="security-heading">Security issue?</h2>
			<p>
				If you've found a security vulnerability, <strong>please report
				it privately</strong> through GitHub's Security Advisories — not
				through public issues.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/security/advisories/new" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
					Report a security vulnerability
				</a>
			</p>
			<p>
				Private reports let us fix the issue before it becomes public
				knowledge. We'll acknowledge your report and work on a fix as
				quickly as we can.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     ACADEMIC INTEGRITY
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="deep" aria-labelledby="integrity-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="integrity-heading">A note on academic integrity</h2>

			<aside class="callout callout--warning" role="note" aria-labelledby="tos-warning">
				<p class="callout__title" id="tos-warning">This tool likely violates Coursera's Terms of Service</p>
				<p>
					Coursera's
					<a href="https://www.coursera.org/about/terms" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Terms of Use</a>
					and
					<a href="https://www.coursera.org/about/terms#honor-code" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Honor Code</a>
					prohibit using automated tools or external assistance on
					graded assessments. Using Auto-Coursera on graded quizzes
					or exams almost certainly falls under that prohibition.
					We're telling you this upfront so you can make an informed
					decision.
				</p>
			</aside>

			<h3>Detection risk</h3>
			<p>
				No tool is invisible. Here's what you should know:
			</p>
			<ul>
				<li>
					<strong>Submission patterns</strong> — Coursera can see how
					quickly you answer questions and your accuracy patterns
					across attempts. Answering every question correctly in
					seconds is not a normal human pattern.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Institutional monitoring</strong> — Many universities
					and employers use their own proctoring software, browser
					lockdowns, or monitoring tools on top of Coursera. These
					operate independently and may flag extension activity.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Browser fingerprinting</strong> — Browser extensions
					leave traces. Sophisticated monitoring can detect the
					presence of extensions, DOM modifications, or unusual page
					interactions.
				</li>
				<li>
					<strong>Network traffic</strong> — The extension itself does
					not phone home or contact any server besides your chosen AI
					provider (using your own API key). But this doesn't mean
					your usage is undetectable by other means.
				</li>
			</ul>

			<h3>Your responsibility</h3>
			<p>
				The developers provide the tool. You decide how to use it, and
				you assume all risk that comes with that decision. We don't
				monitor usage, collect data, or have any way to know how you
				use the extension.
			</p>
			<p>
				<strong>Recommended use:</strong> practice quizzes,
				self-assessment, corporate training retakes, and learning
				reinforcement — situations where the quiz is a gate, not a goal.
				Using it on proctored exams or high-stakes graded assessments
				carries real risk of academic consequences.
			</p>

			<h3>Check your institution's policy</h3>
			<p>
				Academic integrity policies vary widely. Some institutions
				explicitly forbid any AI assistance, even on ungraded work.
				Others are more permissive. Your institution's policy applies
				regardless of what this tool allows you to do technically.
				Look it up before you decide.
			</p>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     COMMUNITY
	     ================================================================ -->
	<section class="section" data-bg="void" aria-labelledby="community-heading">
		<div class="container-narrow">
			<h2 id="community-heading">Community</h2>
			<p>
				Auto-Coursera is open source. Everything happens in the open on
				GitHub.
			</p>
			<ul class="community-links">
				<li>
					<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						GitHub Repository
					</a>
					— source code, README, and project overview
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/discussions" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						GitHub Discussions
					</a>
					— questions, ideas, and general conversation
				</li>
				<li>
					<a href="https://github.com/NICxKMS/auto-coursera/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
						GitHub Issues
					</a>
					— bug reports and feature requests
				</li>
			</ul>
		</div>
	</section>

	<!-- ================================================================
	     INSTALL CTA
	     ================================================================ -->
	<aside class="install-cta" aria-label="Install Auto-Coursera">
		<p class="install-cta__text">Found what you need? Get started with Auto-Coursera.</p>
		<a href="/install/" class="btn btn--primary">Install Auto-Coursera</a>
	</aside>
</Base>

<style>
	/* ==========================================================================
	   Support Page — Scoped Styles
	   ========================================================================== */

	/* ===== Hero ===== */

	.hero {
		padding-block-start: calc(var(--nav-height) + var(--space-7));
		padding-block-end: var(--space-6);
		background-color: var(--bg-deep);
	}

	.hero h1 {
		margin-block-end: var(--space-4);
	}

	.hero__product {
		font-family: var(--font-mono);
		font-size: var(--text-small);
		color: var(--text-muted);
		text-transform: uppercase;
		letter-spacing: 0.05em;
		margin-block-end: var(--space-2);
	}

	.hero__lead {
		font-size: clamp(1.0625rem, 1rem + 0.25vw, 1.1875rem);
		color: var(--text-secondary);
	}

	/* ===== Sections ===== */

	.section {
		padding-block: var(--space-6);
	}

	.section h2 {
		margin-block-end: var(--space-4);
	}

	.section h3 {
		margin-block-start: var(--space-6);
		margin-block-end: var(--space-3);
	}

	/* ===== Quick Help Grid ===== */

	.help-grid {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr;
		gap: var(--space-4);
		margin-block-start: var(--space-5);
	}

	.help-card {
		display: block;
		padding: var(--space-5);
		background-color: var(--surface);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--border-radius);
		text-decoration: none;
		transition:
			background-color var(--transition-fast),
			border-color var(--transition-fast);
	}

	.help-card:hover {
		background-color: var(--surface-hover);
		border-color: var(--border-accent);
		text-decoration: none;
	}

	.help-card h3 {
		font-family: var(--font-body);
		font-size: var(--text-h3);
		font-weight: var(--weight-bold);
		color: var(--text-primary);
		margin: 0 0 var(--space-2) 0;
	}

	.help-card p {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: var(--text-body);
		margin: 0;
		line-height: var(--leading-normal);
	}

	@media (min-width: 640px) {
		.help-grid {
			grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
		}
	}

	/* ===== FAQ Items ===== */

	details[id] {
		scroll-margin-top: calc(var(--nav-height) + var(--space-4));
	}

	.faq-item {
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		border-radius: var(--border-radius);
		margin-block-end: var(--space-3);
		background-color: var(--surface);
	}

	.faq-item summary {
		padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
		font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
		color: var(--text-primary);
		cursor: pointer;
		list-style: none;
	}

	.faq-item summary::before {
		content: '▸ ';
		color: var(--text-muted);
	}

	.faq-item[open] summary::before {
		content: '▾ ';
	}

	.faq-item summary::-webkit-details-marker {
		display: none;
	}

	.faq-body {
		padding: 0 var(--space-5) var(--space-5);
	}

	.faq-body p {
		margin-block-end: var(--space-3);
	}

	.faq-body p:last-child {
		margin-block-end: 0;
	}

	.faq-body ol,
	.faq-body ul {
		margin-block: var(--space-3);
	}

	.faq-body li {
		font-size: var(--text-body);
		margin-block: var(--space-2);
	}

	.faq-body strong {
		color: var(--text-primary);
	}

	/* ===== Community Links ===== */

	.community-links {
		margin-block-start: var(--space-4);
		padding-inline-start: var(--space-5);
	}

	.community-links li {
		margin-block: var(--space-3);
		line-height: var(--leading-normal);
	}

	/* ===== Callout Boxes ===== */

	.callout {
		padding: var(--space-4) var(--space-5);
		border-radius: var(--border-radius);
		border: 1px solid var(--border);
		background-color: var(--surface);
		margin-block-end: var(--space-5);
	}

	.callout__title {
		font-weight: var(--weight-semibold);
		color: var(--text-primary);
		margin-block-end: var(--space-2);
	}

	.callout p {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: var(--text-body);
		line-height: var(--leading-normal);
	}

	.callout--warning {
		border-inline-start: 3px solid var(--warning);
	}

	.callout--warning .callout__title {
		color: var(--warning);
	}

	/* ===== Install CTA ===== */

	.install-cta {
		display: flex;
		flex-direction: column;
		align-items: center;
		gap: var(--space-4);
		padding: var(--space-8) var(--space-5);
		text-align: center;
		border-block-start: 1px solid var(--border);
		background-color: var(--bg-void);
	}

	.install-cta__text {
		color: var(--text-secondary);
		font-size: var(--text-body);
		max-width: 40ch;
	}

	/* ===== Responsive ===== */

	@media (max-width: 480px) {
		.hero {
			padding-block-start: calc(var(--nav-height) + var(--space-6));
			padding-block-end: var(--space-5);
		}
	}
</style>
